### Health check
GET http://localhost:3000/health

### 1. Create a note
POST http://localhost:3000/api/notes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "My first note",
  "content": "This is the content of my first note",
  "tags": ["zettelkasten", "testing"]
}

### 2. Create a note with wikilink reference
POST http://localhost:3000/api/notes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Note with reference",
  "content": "This references [[note-id-123]] in the content",
  "tags": ["references"]
}

### 3. Create a note with minimal fields (no tags)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/notes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Minimal note",
  "content": "Just content, no tags"
}

### 4. Create a note — validation error (empty title)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/notes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "",
  "content": "Some content"
}

### 5. Create a note — validation error (missing content)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/notes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Missing content"
}

### 6. Create a note — validation error (title too long)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/notes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum.",
  "content": "Content"
}

### 7. List all notes
GET http://localhost:3000/api/notes

### 8. Search notes by text
GET http://localhost:3000/api/notes?q=reference

### 9. Search notes by exact title
GET http://localhost:3000/api/notes?title=My first note

### 10. Filter notes by tag
GET http://localhost:3000/api/notes?tag=references

### 11. Get note by ID (replace {{noteId}} with an actual UUID)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/notes/{{noteId}}

### 12. Get note by ID — not found
GET http://localhost:3000/api/notes/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

### 13. Update a note (replace {{noteId}} with an actual UUID)
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/notes/{{noteId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated title",
  "tags": ["updated"]
}

### 14. Update a note — validation error (empty title)
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/notes/{{noteId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": ""
}

### 15. Update a note — not found
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/notes/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Wont work"
}

### 16. Delete a note (replace {{noteId}} with an actual UUID)
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/notes/{{noteId}}

### 17. Delete a note — not found
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/notes/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

### 18. Bulk-replace references globally
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/notes/any-id/references
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "oldId": "note-id-123",
  "newId": "new-note-id-456"
}

### 19. Bulk-replace references — validation error (missing oldId)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/notes/any-id/references
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "newId": "new-id"
}

### 20. Bulk-replace references — validation error (missing newId)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/notes/any-id/references
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "oldId": "old-id"
}
